                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM COOK</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-1230-18440408" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-1230-18440408" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1230-18440408" type="surname" value="LOTTY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1230-18440408" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">CHARLES LOTTY</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18440408-1230-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18440408-1230-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18440408-1230-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> stealing on the <rs id="t18440408-cd-5" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18440408-1230-offence-1 t18440408-cd-5"></join>19th of March</rs>, 23 telescopes, value 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 17<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18440408-name-1103" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1103" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1103" type="surname" value="CETTA"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1103" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18440408-1230-offence-1 t18440408-name-1103"></join>John Cetta</persName>: and </rs>
                  <persName id="def3-1230-18440408" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def3-1230-18440408" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def3-1230-18440408" type="age" value="23"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def3-1230-18440408" type="surname" value="MOORE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def3-1230-18440408" type="given" value="THOMAS ROBERT"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">THOMAS ROBERT MOORE</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18440408-1230-offence-2" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18440408-1230-offence-2" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18440408-1230-offence-2" type="offenceSubcategory" value="receiving"></interp> for feloniously receiving 11 telescopes, part of the same, well knowing them to have been stolen.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1105" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1105" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1105" type="surname" value="CETTA"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1105" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN CETTA</persName>
                  </hi>, <hi rend="italic">telescope-maker, Brook-street, Holborn.</hi> I missed these teles<lb></lb>copes on the 20th of March—they might have been gone a day or two—these are them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What is their value? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> About half-a-crown a piece—I had every reason to suspect one of my servants at first, and that servant told me on the 20th of March, that Cook and Lotty did it, that he had seen them outside the shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1106" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1106" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1106" type="surname" value="EATON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1106" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE EATON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the prosecutor's shop-boy—on the morning of the 19th of March, I had seen Cook and Lotty outside the window for about one minute—I am sure they are the persons—there were three parcels of teles<lb></lb>copes there then—they looked all full—I missed them the next morning—there was a pane of glass broken that they were near to.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1107" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1107" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1107" type="surname" value="ARCHER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1107" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS ARCHER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable G</hi> 8.) I apprehended Lotty on the 22nd—I charged him with stealing telescopes from the prosecutor's window—he said he did not steal them, that he saw Cook and another boy standing against the window, he saw Cook put his hand in, take them out, and give them to another boy, they asked him to go to a chandler's shop on Clerkenwell-green,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184404080171"></xptr>
               <p>and they sold them to a shop<lb></lb>keeper—I then took Cook—he said Eaton gave them to him, and told him his master had given them to him for good conduct—I then took him to the station—he said that Moore was the man he had sold them to—I went to Moore's, and asked him if he had bought any telescopes within the last two or three days—he said, "No"—I said, "I am certain you have, and I have a witness outside that can prove it—he said, opening a chest," "Here are four"—I said, "You have more than that"—he said, "I do not know how many I bought, if you will allow me to look in my book, I will tell you"—he said he bought eleven—he then said he bought one for 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; then six for 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 7 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; and four for 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—I know Mr. Greenwood's handwriting, this is it (<hi rend="italic">deposition read.</hi>)—"The prisoner Cook says, they were brought to me by Lotty, he said he wanted to sell them; on Clerken well-green a boy met Lotty, and told him where he could sell them; we went to Moore's; I sold them to Moore.—Lotty says, it is false; I saw Cook take them out; I did not know what was in them; he asked me to go with him to Turn mill-street.—Moore says, I did not know the value of them, or that they were stolen."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Does not Moore keep a marine-store shop? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, he is a general dealer, he sells cheese, butter, and sweet things for children.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1108" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1108" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1108" type="surname" value="EATON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1108" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE EATON</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I did not give any telescopes to Cook—I spoke to him that morning.</p>
               <p>(The prisoners received good characters.)</p>
